class Solution {
    public int smallestValue(int n) {
        while (true) {
            int sum = 0, temp = n;
            for (int i = 2; i * i <= temp; i++) {
                while (temp % i == 0) {
                    sum += i;
                    temp /= i;
                }
            }
            if (temp > 1) sum += temp;
            if (sum == n) return n;
            n = sum;
        }
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(sqrt(n))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iteratively replaces n with the sum of its prime factors until it reaches a prime number or a number that is equal to the sum of its prime factors, leveraging the property that a number equal to the sum of its prime factors is the smallest value it will take on.
